<div id="ai-in-it" v-cloak>
  <div purpose="page-container">
    <div purpose="page-content">
      <div purpose="page-hero">
        <div purpose="page-heading">
          <h1>Every other device management tool
          was designed before AI existed</h1>
        </div>
        <div purpose="hero-image">
          <img class="d-sm-block d-none" src="/images/ai-in-it-hero-1029x201@2x.png" alt="A timeline of device management tools"><img class="d-block d-sm-none" src="/images/ai-in-it-hero-sm-490x741@2x.png" alt="A timeline of device management tools">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="page-section">
        <div purpose="section-heading" class="text-center">
          <h2>There are two ways to use AI</h2>
          <p>Both help, but one makes a big difference.</p>
        </div>
        <div purpose="feature-cards">
          <div purpose="card">
            <h4>Read only</h4>
            <p>Getting answers in seconds to questions like "Which AI tools are running in my environment?" is helpful, but…</p>
          </div>
          <div purpose="card">
            <h4>Read & write</h4>
            <p>Getting AI to do things like "Enforce these AI controls from InfoSec" makes a bigger impact.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="page-section">
        <div purpose="feature-with-image">
          <div purpose="feature-image">
            <img alt="Decide what stays and what goes" src="/images/ai-assisted-it-feature-image-800x600@2x.png">
          </div>
          <div purpose="feature-text">
            <h2>So what does it take?</h2>
            <p>The AI boost is real. Developers have had it for years, because their work lives in code. IT hasn't.</p>
            <p>Other tools add their own AI, locked inside their console. Fleet lets you manage your devices as code, so you can use the AI you already trust, with every change reviewed before it ships.</p>
            <animated-arrow-button href="/infrastructure-as-code">Manage devices as code</animated-arrow-button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="page-section">
        <div purpose="report-card">
          <div purpose="card-text">
            <div purpose="card-heading">
              <h2>The road to AI in IT</h2>
              <p>We surveyed 500+ IT leaders across 4 regions to find out!</p>
            </div>
            <div purpose="report-statistics">
              <div purpose="statistic">
                <div purpose="percentage">46%</div>
                <div purpose="statistic-text">rank AI automation as their top priority.</div>
              </div>
              <div purpose="statistic">
                <div purpose="percentage">79%</div>
                <div purpose="statistic-text">take more than a day to patch a critical vulnerability.</div>
              </div>
              <div purpose="statistic">
                <div purpose="percentage">13%</div>
                <div purpose="statistic-text">manage everything from a single platform. The rest run three or more tools.</div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <a purpose="section-button" target="_blank" href="/pdfs/Fleet-IT-leadership-report_the-road-to-AI-in-IT.pdf" no-icon>Read the report</a>
          </div>

          <div purpose="card-image">

          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div purpose="page-section">
        <div purpose="bottom-cta">
          <div purpose="page-heading">
            <h1>Manage your devices as code</h1>
          </div>
          <p>Talk to us about your fleet, or get hands-on at a free in-person workshop.</p>
          <div purpose="button-row">
            <a purpose="cta-button" href="/contact">Get a demo</a>
            <animated-arrow-button href="/workshops">Get certified</animated-arrow-button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <cloud-city></cloud-city>

</div>
<%- /* Expose server-rendered data as window.SAILS_LOCALS :: */ exposeLocalsToBrowser() %>
